OL,3,CJersey government criticised for
OL,4,C#111.8m spend on consultants
OL,6,FWhile the report said consultants can
OL,7,Fprovide great benefits when used
OL,8,Fcorrectly, misuse can drain budgets
OL,9,F"very quickly", stating has become too
OL,10,Freliant on consultants for non-major
OL,11,Fprojects.
OL,13,FThe report also found #111.8m was
OL,14,Fspent on healthcare consultancy from
OL,15,F2019 to 2022.
OL,17,FFor example, the Team Jersey project,
OL,18,Fdesigned to train more managers to
OL,19,Fmove away from consultants within the
OL,20,Fgovernment, ironically cost #1.8m in
OL,21,Fconsultancy fees.
