OL,3,CJersey government criticised for
OL,4,C#111.8m spend on consultants
OL,6,FOther recommendations include
OL,7,Fidentifying skill gaps in key areas,
OL,8,Fand reviewing how consultants will be
OL,9,Fused in the future.
OL,11,FChief Minister Lyndon Farnham has said
OL,12,Freducing this spending is a "high
OL,13,Fpriority".
OL,15,FHe added: "We currently have over 200
OL,16,Fprojects being run by the government
OL,17,Finvolving consultants and that's
OL,18,Fsomething we are going to address as a
OL,19,Fmatter of priority."
